  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "RESTAURANT CAPTAIN",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><p>We are looking for a capable and experienced <strong>Restrarent caption</strong> to take full responsibility for the operational success of our outlet. This role requires strong leadership, daily presence on the ground, and a deep understanding of customer service, hygiene, and food operations.</p><p>If you’ve previously led a team in a busy restaurant environment and know how to run a shift from opening to closing, we want to hear from you.</p><p><u><strong>Minimum Requirements (Strict Filtering)</strong></u></p><p>· At least 15<strong> years of experience in the F&B industry</strong>, with a minimum 10 <strong>years in</strong></p><p><strong>a managerial or supervisory position</strong></p><p>· Hands-on experience managing kitchen and front-of-house teams in a dine-in setup</p><p>· Familiar with shift planning, manpower deployment, and real-time staff supervision</p><p>· Skilled in <strong>inventory handling</strong>, supplier coordination, and stock-level monitoring</p><p>· Well-versed in <strong>food hygiene standards, licensing matters</strong>, and day-to-day cleanliness inspections</p><p>· Comfortable handling customer feedback and responding professionally to complaints or issues</p><p>· Proficient in using POS systems and maintaining outlet-level sales or petty cash records</p><p>· Available to work weekends, evenings, and public holidays as part of regular roster</p><p>· Physically fit and willing to be actively involved on the restaurant floor</p><p><u><strong>Experience That Will Give You an Edge</strong></u></p><p>· Previous experience with <strong>new outlet setups</strong>, launching menus, or opening branches</p><p>· Able to conduct staff training and implement SOPs independently</p><p>· Familiarity with central kitchen operations or delivery order integration systems</p><p>· Track record of improving outlet performance or reducing wastage/costs</p><p>· Knowledge of simple reporting tools (Google Sheets, Excel) for daily tracking</p><p><u><strong>Perks of Joining Our Team</strong></u></p><p>· You’ll take ownership of the restaurant like it’s your own</p><p>· Management will support you with systems, supplies, and hiring when needed</p><p>· Gain exposure to outlet-level budgeting, purchasing, and promotions</p><p>· Career pathway available to <strong>Multi-Outlet Manager</strong> or <strong>F&B Operations Lead</strong></p><p>· Uniforms provided, meals included during shifts, and support staff on duty</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
